Going to be setting up some images to I can rapidly BLAST or align large amounts of sequences since I'm an impatient fuck. 

Set up the instance in the EC2 control panel, 600 Gb storage, C5.16Xlarge (need that sweet sweet RAM and 27 CPU cores) - this can be swapped to a z1d.6xlarge for single threaded processes. 

Upon boot up, connect via: ssh -i "/Users/awsms1/RNA lab/EC2 big boi/Powerlifter.pem" ec2-user@18.117.114.19

Install the required programs: 

usearch (artems copy):  scp -i "/Users/awsms1/RNA lab/EC2 big boi/Powerlifter.pem" "/Users/awsms1/RNA lab/usearch64" ec2-user@18.117.114.19:~
                        mkdir -p ~/bin
                        mv usearch64 ~/bin/usearch

BLAST install: wget https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/blast/executables/blast+/LATEST/ncbi-blast-2.17.0+-x64-linux.tar.gz
               tar -xzf ncbi-blast-2.17.0+-x64-linux.tar.gz
               sudo mv ncbi-blast-2.17.0+ /usr/local/ncbi-blast+
               echo 'export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/ncbi-blast+/bin' >> ~/.bashrc
               source ~/.bashrc

BLAST nt db install: sudo yum install perl-CPAN -y

Crack open Screen:   screen -S blastdb_download
                     update_blastdb.pl --decompress nt

Detach: Ctrl + A, then D
To reattach: screen -r blastdb_download


                     
